TL;DR Elves and hackers, rejoice!

Wot I liked
- Cyberpunk + elves and orcs - what no to like;
- You can choose from several archetypes, which are highly modifiable: be a techno bullet spewing or katana wielding samurai, a drone daddy rigger, a neo hacker decker, a cyber mage, a psi monk, a charming huckster or mix and match of all the above;
- While most dialogue options don't mean much (usually), they allow you to roleplay your brand of a shadowrunner. Some dialogue line matter, and your skill, stats and items also play a role;
- A "typical" noire detective story: your friend is calling upon your help from beyond the grave, serial killers, mad scientists, deranged doctors, depraved technoaddicts, evil cults and corps, troll gangbangers, elf hackers - it got it all;
- Map Editor! Giving the players an ability to make their own stories within the setting is laudable;
- If you like to read you're gonna experience a well-written interesting story with cool characters living in an insane world;
- Metavere... ahem... the Matrix! Tron-like cyberworld of duels with virus attacks and cypher shields;
- Beautiful backdrops of various cyberpunk locales of a futuristic megacity;
- You typical bladerunner megacorp-run world, where you're but a tiny insignificant spec trying to grab a chewy morsel and not become a chewy morsel for others.

Wot I disliked
- Few keyboard shortcuts, none are customizable (use AHK!);
- The main problem of SR is its scale - too damn small: there're no long side quests or seedy cyberdens to explore (apart from the presented in the main quest of course), the itemisation comprises several dozen items, weapons and gear and spells altogether;
- Clunkiness of the UI multiplied by the inhospitableness of the combat system;
- Bugs and glitches;
- The combat system, item assortment, tactical choices leave much to be desired;
- Some chicanery with the saving system - it just does not work right.

To sum it all up, while it's not a very interesting game, I'd still give it thumbs-up for the setting and story alone. I hope that next 2 instalments will have an improvement in the combat depth, exploration and GUI friendliness.

