This game works as an intro to the Shadowrun world:
- Amazing, very well written story;
- Imersive, fells like you are living that story because of how good it is and because you have choices on how to get things done;
- Lots of skills for you to use;
- Master 1 or 2 skills or do a bit of everything;
- Beautifull futuristic, post apocalyptic locations in and around future Seattle.
- Cheap game with steamkeys or on sale.

The only bad thing is that the game is quite small (10h-13h depending on your aproach) and quite linear.
But again this work like a intro game and it's quite cheap on sale + being on a bundle with all other Shadowrun.
